      "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/tarball/v0.5.2-beta",
      "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/zipball/v0.5.2-beta",
      "body": "# A software tool for calculating energy efficiency for a variety of industrial and manufacturing applications.\r\n\r\nThe Department of Energy (DOE) Advanced Manufacturing Office (AMO) has undertaken an effort to refactor legacy tools that were written for the Windows platform into a modern environment. The legacy tools were written in a variety of programming languages, and the source code considered proprietary. This meant that updating them was a difficult task. \r\n\r\nMEASUR helps manufacturers increase industrial energy efficiency at the plant-level and in specific systems. Learn step-by-step ways to identify opportunities, monitor progress, and improve efficiency in any facility. Some tools help facilities implement an energy management system and prepare to become ISO 50001 and Superior Energy Performance certified.\r\n\r\n\r\nApplication:\r\n* Added:  Google translate functionality in settings to translate application\r\n* Fixed: Bug for exporting facility info when \"selecting all\" folder contents\r\n\r\nPumps:\r\n* Updated: Assessment help text for VFD\r\n* Added: System curve equation \r\n\r\nProcess Heating:\r\n* Fixed: Inconsistencies between Efficiency Improvement Calculator and O2 Enrichment calculator\r\n\r\nFans Analysis Calculator:\r\n* Fixed: Unit conversions\r\n* Enhanced: Navigation\r\n* Added: Plane diagram for different plane types\r\n* Added: Highlighting of table and diagram depending on plane input tab\r\n\r\nFans:\r\n* Added: New fan analysis calculator to modal for calculating pressures and flow rate\r\n* Fixed: Compressibility factor calculation in metric\r\n\r\nSteam:\r\n* Updated: Unit conversions to match suite, using units for energy in kJ \r\n* Added: Modal for calculating blowdown rate given conductivity\r\n* Fixed: Inlet water value display in diagram\r\n* Fixed: Wrong table displaying from clicking Low Pressure PRV outlet arrow\r\n\r\nTreasure Hunt - \r\n* New Calculator: \"Waste Water Reduction\" calculator added\r\n* New Calculator: \"Compressed Air Pressure Reduction\" calculator added\r\n* Fixed: Treasure Hunt example being reset when all examples are reset\r\n* Updated: Descriptions of calculators\r\n* Enhanced: Selecting utility types used in assessment in setup\r\n\r\nCalculators:\r\n* Fixed: Many spelling and grammar errors in calcluators\r\n* Fixed: Space between letters and exponents\r\n* Updated: More meaningful calculator descriptions\r\n* Fixed: Floating semicolon in some options for unit converter\r\n* Added: New pump curve icon\r\n* Fixed: Validation for steam properties calculator\r\n* Fixed: Percent load estimation calculation\r\n* Fixed: Flash tank validation be method selection\r\n* Enhanced: Replaced \"Quantity Value\" with \"Known Variable\" label for steam calculators\r\n* Fixed: Ordering of header results table\r\n* Fixed: Pre Assessment Screening result units for Energy Cost\r\n\r\nKnown Issues:\r\n* The Mac and Linux releases have significantly slower app start times than windows\r\n* Renaming an export in Windows Download menu can delete the file extension (.json)\r\n* Assessments made in a previous release may experience errors\r\n* Import files made in a previous release may not be usable\r\n\r\nWindows MD5 Hash: 36f6f06647f1b933d4b7b75c0782b4cb"
