      "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/tarball/v0.5.1-beta",
      "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/zipball/v0.5.1-beta",
      "body": "# A software tool for calculating energy efficiency for a variety of industrial and manufacturing applications.\r\n\r\nThe Department of Energy (DOE) Advanced Manufacturing Office (AMO) has undertaken an effort to refactor legacy tools that were written for the Windows platform into a modern environment. The legacy tools were written in a variety of programming languages, and the source code considered proprietary. This meant that updating them was a difficult task. \r\n\r\nMEASUR helps manufacturers increase industrial energy efficiency at the plant-level and in specific systems. Learn step-by-step ways to identify opportunities, monitor progress, and improve efficiency in any facility. Some tools help facilities implement an energy management system and prepare to become ISO 50001 and Superior Energy Performance certified.\r\n\r\n\r\nApplication:\r\n* Fixed - Auto updater bug disabling auto-updater for v0.5.0-beta\r\n* Updated - Acknowledgments page\r\n* Updated - Electron version\r\n* Updated - Bootstrap version\r\n* Updated - Removed ng-toasty dependency\r\n* Enhanced - Formatting cleanup for the results displays\r\n\r\nPumps:\r\n* Added: Beta Disclaimer\r\n* Added: Warning popup when a scenario was created in Expert view but viewed in Novice view\r\n\r\nProcess Heating:\r\n* Fixed: Help text for Explore Opportunities was missing\r\n* Fixed: Notes in Explore Opportunities was missing\r\n* Enhanced: Various HTML CSS enhancements to match PSAT and FSAT\r\n* Enhanced: Added help text diagram to several fields in flue gas calculator to better explain how to obtain data\r\n\r\nFans:\r\n\r\n\r\nSteam:\r\n* Fixed: Import Power and Makeup Water Costs were missing from Results \"Input Summary\"\r\n* Fixed: Name of \"High to Medium Pressure Turbine\" in Results \"Input Summary\"\r\n* Fixed: Issue with steam unit conversions\r\n* Fixed: Steam results were not updating properly in Assessment\r\n* Fixed: Issue where scenarios where changes were made to turbines were not displaying properly in Explore Opportunities\r\n* Fixed: Bug regarding copying modifications not carrying over changes to baseline\r\n* Fixed: Issue where marginal steam cost button was not calculating marginal steam costs\r\n* Fixed: Inclusion of $ before \"Electricity Imported\" result in steam diagram results\r\n* Fixed: Issue where HP header warning icon was not sticking to HP header in diagram\r\n* Fixed: Issue regarding extra data generation when making new scenarios resulting in not being able to export assessments with several scenarios\r\n* Added: Steam to rollup report functionality\r\n* Added: Indicators for zero flow to diagram \r\n* Added: Clicking on a pipe or arrow within pipe will put the summary data in the results tab on the right \r\n* Added: Beta Disclaimer\r\n* Added: Warning popup when a scenario was created in Expert view but viewed in Novice view\r\n* Added: Message in report graphs if there are no turbines to generate a turbine pie chart\r\n* Enhanced: Minor adjustments to system diagram to improve visibility of displayed values\r\n* Enhanced: Changed wording of two fields names \"Desuperheat into ... pressure header\" to \"Desuperheat out of ... pressure header\"\r\n* Enhanced: Additional warnings to diagram if steam in header/equipment is saturated, cannot flash water, etc.\r\n* Enhanced: User input validation warnings for various potential input errors\r\n* Enhanced: Ability to zoom in and out on the diagram\r\n\r\nTreasure Hunt - \r\n* New Feature - Treasure Hunt Calculators - allows users to estimate the energy savings for various opportunities and compare current energy use throughout facility to that after opportunity implementation\r\n\r\nCalculators:\r\n* Fixed: Several bugs relating Pump/Fan and System curves\r\n* Fixed: Bug where the decimal point was not recognized in replace/rewind motor calculator\r\n* Added: Cost of electricity/fuel and cost savings to various calculator (lighting, replace motors, etc.)\r\n* Added: Electricity, natural gas, and compressed air reduction calculators\r\n* Enhanced: Combined replace/rewind motor calculator and replace motor calculators\r\n* Enhanced: Several calculators to fit into the Treasure Hunt (lighting, replace motors, etc.)\r\n* Enhanced: Description of Combined Heat and Power Calculator\r\n\r\nKnown Issues:\r\n* The calculations for the Steam application will take longer than the others due to its iterative calculations\r\n* The Mac and Linux releases have significantly slower app start times than in previous builds\r\n* Renaming an export in Windows Download menu can delete the file extension (.json)\r\n* Assessments made in a previous release may experience errors\r\n* Import files made in a previous release will not be useable"
