      "tarball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/tarball/v0.4.0-beta",
      "zipball_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/ORNL-AMO/AMO-Tools-Desktop/zipball/v0.4.0-beta",
      "body": "# A software tool for calculating energy efficiency for a variety of industrial and manufacturing applications.\r\nThe Department of Energy (DOE) Advanced Manufacturing Office (AMO) has undertaken an effort to refactor legacy tools that were written for the Windows platform into a modern environment. The legacy tools were written in a variety of programming languages, and the source code considered proprietary. This meant that updating them was a difficult task. \r\nMEASUR helps manufacturers increase industrial energy efficiency at the plant-level and in specific systems. Learn step-by-step ways to identify opportunities, monitor progress, and improve efficiency in any facility. Some tools help facilities implement an energy management system and prepare to become ISO 50001 and Superior Energy Performance certified.\r\n\r\n**Application:**\r\n* Added: Popup to home page to ask for tool feedback\r\n* Added: Tutorial Setting for \"All Hide/Show\"\r\n* Enhanced: Changed name of \"Contact\" page to \"Feedback\" and added link for tool feedback survey\r\n* Enhanced: Style updates for consistency throughout the tool\r\n* Enhanced: Added button for \"Copy Table\" to most tables throughout tool\r\n* Enhanced: Esc button now closes popup graphs\r\n* Fixed: Several grammar/spelling issues in tool\r\n\r\n**Pumps:**\r\n* Fixed: Bug relating to using the backspace to clear the name of a new scenario in Explore Opportunities\r\n* Fixed: Clarified that \"Cost\" field in Field Data is \"Electricity Cost\"\r\n\r\n**Process Heating:**\r\n* Enhanced: Help text for \"Number of Phases\" in Aux Equipment\r\n* Fixed: Updated field title for \"Motor Phase\" field in Aux Equipment to \"Number of Phases\"\r\n\r\n**Fans:**\r\n* Fixed: Updated field title for \"Cost\" field in Field Data to \"Electricity Cost\"\r\n\r\n**Steam:**\r\n* New Feature - Steam System Modeling Tool - allows users to compare current steam systems to modified scenarios to analyze potential energy savings\r\n* Added - Steam Reports and dynamic diagram\r\n\r\n**Calculators:**\r\n* Added: Lighting Calculator to home screen\r\n* Enhanced: Styling of Motor - Replace/Rewind to fit into the Treasure Hunt Styling\r\n* Enhanced: Help text for Compressed Air - Bag Method calculator and Compressed Air - System Capacity calculator\r\n* Enhanced: Reduced the maximum width of the unit converter calculator\r\n* Enhanced: Set the right side of the unit converter to a result instead of an updating input field\r\n* Enhanced: Styling of Motor - Replace Existing motor to fit into the Treasure Hunt Styling\r\n* Enhanced: Calculator help text for Process Heating - O2 Enrichment & Efficiency Improvement\r\n* Fixed: Bug where field help text was not always showing up in pre-assessment calculator\r\n* Fixed: Bug in pump & fan curves and system curves where tool was not converting from non-standard imperial units before sending it to the suite for calculations\r\n* Fixed: Suite bug where the Steam - Flash Tank calculator would not properly identify if incoming steam was superheated or saturated, leading to errors\r\n* Fixed: Several small bugs relating to calculator icons\r\n* Fixed: Bug relating to the Fan - Fan Analysis calculator not allowing progression when using \"Use Custom Density\"\r\n\r\n**Known Issues:**\r\n* The calculations for the Steam application will take longer than the others due to its iterative calculations\r\n* The Mac and Linux releases have significantly slower app start times than in previous builds\r\n* Renaming an export in Windows Download menu can delete the file extension (.json)\r\n* Assessments made in a previous release may experience errors\r\n* Import files made in a previous release will not be useable"
